26#include <sys/cdefs.h>
27__KERNEL_RCSID(0, "$NetBSD: nouveau_nvkm_subdev_pci_nv46.c,v 1.2 2018/08/27 04:58:34 riastradh Exp $");
28
29#include "priv.h"
30
31#include <core/pci.h>
32
33/* MSI re-arm through the PRI appears to be broken on NV46/NV50/G84/G86/G92,
34 * so we access it via alternate PCI config space mechanisms.
35 */
36void
37nv46_pci_msi_rearm(struct nvkm_pci *pci)
38{
39 struct nvkm_device *device = pci->subdev.device;
40 struct pci_dev *pdev = device->func->pci(device)->pdev;
41 pci_write_config_byte(pdev, 0x68, 0xff);
42}
43
44static const struct nvkm_pci_func
45nv46_pci_func = {
46 .rd32 = nv40_pci_rd32,
47 .wr08 = nv40_pci_wr08,
48 .wr32 = nv40_pci_wr32,
49 .msi_rearm = nv46_pci_msi_rearm,
50};
51
52int
53nv46_pci_new(struct nvkm_device *device, int index, struct nvkm_pci **ppci)
54{
55 return nvkm_pci_new_(&nv46_pci_func, device, index, ppci);
56}
